com.underlegendz.corelegendz.utils

Class AnimationUtils.AnimationEndListener

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.underlegendz.corelegendz.utils.AnimationUtils.AnimationEndListener
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.view.animation.Animation.AnimationListener
    Enclosing class:
    AnimationUtils

    public abstract static class AnimationUtils.AnimationEndListener
extends java.lang.Object
implements android.view.animation.Animation.AnimationListener
    A custom listener that implements AnimationListener and overrides onAnimationStart() and onAnimationRepeat() leaving their bodies empty. It can be used in place of AnimationListener if you only need to override onAnimationEnd(), avoiding thus having to add pointless boilerplate code to your class. Whenever you need to do something after the animation is over but not when it starts nor while the animation is in progress, you can add an AnimationEndListener to your Animation like this: 
     animation.setAnimationListener(new AnimationEndListener() {
      Override
      public void onAnimationEnd(Animation animation) {
          //Code to be executed when animation ends.
      }
 });
